name: Evergreen State Fairgrounds Covid-19 Vaccine Site
info:
**THIS IS A MODERNA CLINIC ONLY**
Starting April 15, 2021, everyone 16 and older in Washington is eligible for COVID-19 vaccination.

Please also note that, you must be 18 or older for the Moderna vaccine. 

Vaccination at these sites is by appointment only for those eligible in the current phase.  Be prepared to provide identification as well as appointment confirmation at check-in.  Please arrive no more than 10 minutes prior to your appointment time. Expect to stay between 15-30 minutes after you receive your vaccine to monitor for any adverse reaction. Medical staff will be on hand. A mask must be worn at all times during the appointment, and please wear clothing with short or loose sleeves.

****IF YOU ARE SCHEDULING YOUR 2ND DOSE APPOINTMENT, YOU MUST PROVIDE PROOF OF 1ST DOSE (example: vaccination card, medical record, myir.net immunization record)****
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Onestop Medical Clinic - Covid Vaccination Venue
info:
• This is a Community service our Clinic is providing as a give back in the current difficult situation since January 2021. Please DO NOT disrespect our hardworking staff and volunteers. No profanity please.
	
	• Due to the social distancing limitations and limited parking, please plan to arrive NO earlier than 5 Minutes. Please DO NOT park in front of our neighbor’s building; 1316 Central Ave S. The extra public parking is available next door at the Kent Municipal Court (1220 Central Ave S, Kent, WA 98032).
	
	• In order to better serve you and make your wait time shorter, could you please print, fill, sign and bring the forms to be sent by email post your registration along with you for your appointment? 
	
	• We ask that for everyone’s safety, please DO NOT visit this vaccination drive without an appointment. Please DO NOT email or call us to inquire, schedule, reschedule, cancel your appointment about COVID-19 Vaccine as we are experiencing extremely high email and call volumes. Please DO NOT book an appointment from the Zocodoc or Onestop Medical's website for COVID-19 Immunization.
	
	• Please allow up to Two Weeks to schedule you for Dose 2. Please note Dose 1 and Dose 2 are at least 17 days apart. Please DO NOT laminate the vaccine card. 
 
	• Please remember that you will need to bring your photo ID/Passport, medical insurance card (if insured). If you're receiving your 2nd vaccination, you will be required to bring your vaccination card too.

	• We DO NOT accept any form of payment, donation for COVID-19 vaccine from any patient. Please DO NOT make any payment to the Onestop Medical. If you receive a bill for your COVID vaccine, please contact your insurance company First.
	If you DO NOT have an insurance, no worries and you will still receive your vaccine.
	If you have Insurance a small Admin Fee will be charged to the insurance. The patient DOES NOT PAY for any vaccine related services out-of-pocket  The Admin Fee will be used to help cover a portion of the cost to maintain the staff, PPEs and all medical need.
	
	https://www.doh.wa.gov/Emergencies/COVID19/VaccineInformation/VaccineCost#heading67668
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Rebel Med NW - COVID Vaccine Clinic
address: 5401 Leary Ave NW STE 202, Seattle WA, 98107
info:
***We will accept both first and second dose appointments*** ***Please notify us of a cancelation ASAP, we have patients on waiting list, and would prefer not to waste vaccines*** You must provide insurance (photo ID if you do not have insurance) by one of the 2 methods below before you check-in for vaccine. Upload options 1. Prepmod at time of sign up 2. bring your insurance card to your visit.

We are administering the first/second dose of the Moderna vaccine. Moderna is currently approved for all adults 18 years and older. Please bring a face covering that covers the mouth and nose. Everyone is required to stay 15-30 minutes under observation after receiving the vaccine.

Rebel Med NW is located on the 2nd floor, with the entrance on NW Vernon Place. Across the street from the Olympic Athletic Club. We are an integrative medical clinic specializing in Naturopathic Primary Care, Acupuncture, and Mind Body Medicine. Please be respectful of the space as treatments may be ongoing. Please contact 206-297-6013, and ask to speak to a provider on call if you have a question, leave a voicemail and we will return as soon as we are available.

Call 911 if life-threatening emergency, and you are in need of immediate help.
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Benton Franklin - Kennewick COVID Vaccine Clinic
info: ******Pfizer Clinic***** All patients 16 years old and older can register. If you are 16-17 years old you must be with a parent or guardian or verbal parental/guardian consent. **FOR 2ND DOSE PLEASE BRING YOUR COVID-19 VACCINATION RECORD CARD** For Both 1st and 2nd dose - Please bring your appointment confirmation. Please do not come if you are feeling ill. Given the limited supply of COVID-19 vaccine available at this time and Washington's commitment to equitable and fair access, those seeking COVID-19 vaccines at this clinic location you must either live or work in Washington state. If you do not live or work in Washington, please do not make an appointment or travel to this site. You may be asked to provide something that shows you live or work in Washington, such as a utility bill; a voucher from your employer; or your work, school, or state ID. The site will not make a copy or record this information in any way. This is only to show that you currently live or work in Washington. ---- **Masks are required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided. Follow posted signage about traffic and parking at the site. **Enter the fairgrounds from 10th Street.** If you have lost your vaccination record card, please go to https://wa.myir.net
special: If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
